<style>
.faqp-page { padding-top: 120px; padding-bottom: 5rem; background: #1c1a1a; color: #fff; min-height: 100vh; }
.faqp-wrap { max-width: 820px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 1.5rem; }

.faqp-hero { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 3.5rem; padding-bottom: 2.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.06); }
.faqp-hero__eyebrow { font-size: 0.7rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.32em; color: var(--accent-gold, #dea882); margin: 0 0 1rem; }
.faqp-hero__title { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.2rem); font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.2; margin: 0 0 1.25rem; color: #fff; font-style: italic; }
.faqp-hero__lead { font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.8; color: rgba(255,255,255,.68); max-width: 620px; margin: 0 auto; }
.faqp-hero__lead a { color: var(--accent-gold, #dea882); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 3px; }

.faqp-category { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
.faqp-category__title { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(1.3rem, 3vw, 1.65rem); font-weight: 400; color: var(--accent-gold, #dea882); margin: 0 0 1.5rem; padding-bottom: .75rem; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(222,168,130,.2); font-style: italic; }

.faqp-item { border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.06); }
.faqp-item[open] .faqp-question::after { transform: rotate(225deg); }
.faqp-question { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; gap: 1rem; padding: 1.25rem 0; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 500; color: #fff; cursor: pointer; list-style: none; user-select: none; transition: color .25s ease; }
.faqp-question::-webkit-details-marker, .faqp-question::marker { display: none; content: ''; }
.faqp-question::after { content: ''; flex-shrink: 0; width: 10px; height: 10px; border-right: 1px solid var(--accent-gold, #dea882); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--accent-gold, #dea882); transform: rotate(45deg); transition: transform .3s ease; margin-top: -4px; }
.faqp-question:hover { color: var(--accent-gold, #dea882); }

.faqp-answer { padding: 0 0 1.5rem; font-size: .95rem; line-height: 1.85; color: rgba(255,255,255,.68); }
.faqp-answer p { margin: 0 0 .75rem; }
.faqp-answer p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
.faqp-answer a { color: var(--accent-gold, #dea882); text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(222,168,130,.3); transition: border-color .25s ease; }
.faqp-answer a:hover { border-color: var(--accent-gold, #dea882); }

.faqp-cta { text-align: center; margin-top: 4rem; padding: 3rem 2rem; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.06); }
.faqp-cta__title { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 3.5vw, 1.85rem); font-weight: 400; color: #fff; margin: 0 0 1rem; font-style: italic; }
.faqp-cta__text { font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.75; color: rgba(255,255,255,.68); max-width: 520px; margin: 0 auto 1.75rem; }
.faqp-cta__btn { display: inline-block; padding: .9rem 2.5rem; font-size: .78rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: .22em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #1c1a1a; background: var(--accent-gold, #dea882); border: none; border-radius: 2px; text-decoration: none; transition: background .3s ease, transform .2s ease; }
.faqp-cta__btn:hover { background: var(--accent-gold-light, #e8bf9e); transform: translateY(-1px); }

@media (max-width: 600px) {
  .faqp-page { padding-top: 100px; }
  .faqp-question { font-size: .92rem; padding: 1rem 0; }
  .faqp-answer { font-size: .9rem; }
  .faqp-cta { padding: 2.5rem 1rem; }
}
</style>

<section class="faqp-page">
  <div class="faqp-wrap">

    <header class="faqp-hero">
      <p class="faqp-hero__eyebrow">From the atelier</p>
      <h1 class="faqp-hero__title">Frequently asked</h1>
      <p class="faqp-hero__lead">A few questions we are asked most often — about the stones, the jewellery, ordering, and how the atelier works. If your question is not here, <a href="mailto:hello@lauramilman.com">write to us</a> — we answer every message personally.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="faqp-category">
      <h2 class="faqp-category__title">On the stones</h2>

      <details class="faqp-item">
        <summary class="faqp-question">Are lab-grown diamonds real diamonds?</summary>
        <div class="faqp-answer">
          <p>Yes. Lab-grown diamonds are real diamonds — chemically, physically, and optically identical to those formed in the earth. The same pure carbon crystal, the same brilliance, the same Mohs 10 hardness. The only difference is origin: ours are grown in a controlled facility rather than mined.</p>
          <p>Every centre stone we set is independently graded by IGI or GIA, using the same standards applied to mined stones. More on this in <a href="/pages/why-lab-grown">On Diamond Origin</a>.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faqp-item">
        <summary class="faqp-question">How are lab-grown diamonds made?</summary>
        <div class="faqp-answer">
          <p>Two methods produce them: Chemical Vapor Deposition (CVD) and High Pressure High Temperature (HPHT). Both replicate the conditions under which diamonds form — intense heat and pressure — over weeks rather than billions of years.</p>
          <p>CVD begins with a thin diamond seed in a chamber filled with carbon-rich gas; carbon atoms deposit onto the seed, building a crystal layer by layer. HPHT uses a press to apply extreme pressure and temperature to a carbon source, crystallising it into diamond around a seed. The result in either case is a real carbon crystal with the same atomic structure as any diamond found in nature.</p>
          <p>For more, see our <a href="/pages/buying-guide">guide to diamonds</a>.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faqp-item">
        <summary class="faqp-question">Do your stones come with certificates?</summary>
        <div class="faqp-answer">
          <p>Always. Every Laura Milman centre stone arrives with an independent certificate from IGI or GIA, detailing cut, color, clarity, and carat weight — graded to the same standards as mined diamonds. The certificate is included with your piece and can be verified directly through the issuing laboratory.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faqp-item">
        <summary class="faqp-question">How do lab-grown diamonds compare to natural ones?</summary>
        <div class="faqp-answer">
          <p>Identical to the naked eye, and to nearly every gemological instrument. They share the same chemical composition, crystal structure, hardness, refractive index, and brilliance as mined diamonds. A trained gemologist with specialised equipment can distinguish them by microscopic growth markers, but in terms of beauty, durability, and sparkle, they are the same stone.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faqp-item">
        <summary class="faqp-question">Will a lab-grown diamond pass a diamond tester?</summary>
        <div class="faqp-answer">
          <p>Yes. Standard diamond testers measure thermal or electrical conductivity — properties that lab-grown diamonds share with mined ones. They test as real diamonds because they are real diamonds.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>

    <div class="faqp-category">
      <h2 class="faqp-category__title">On the jewellery</h2>

      <details class="faqp-item">
        <summary class="faqp-question">What metals do you work in?</summary>
        <div class="faqp-answer">
          <p>We work in 14k and 18k gold — white, yellow, and rose — and in platinum. Each metal is selected by the master setter for the piece in hand: platinum for everyday durability, 18k gold for the warmth and depth of colour, 14k where the design calls for a slightly harder alloy.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faqp-item">
        <summary class="faqp-question">Where are your pieces made?</summary>
        <div class="faqp-answer">
          <p>Each piece is designed and finished by hand in our New York atelier by master setters from the Milman family workshop. Nothing is contracted out and nothing is assembled abroad.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faqp-item">
        <summary class="faqp-question">May I commission a bespoke piece?</summary>
        <div class="faqp-answer">
          <p>The Milman atelier has been making one-of-one pieces for three generations. Send a sketch, an inspiration image, or simply a description to <a href="mailto:hello@lauramilman.com">hello@lauramilman.com</a>, and we will guide you through the process, timeline, and cost.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faqp-item">
        <summary class="faqp-question">What ring sizes do you offer?</summary>
        <div class="faqp-answer">
          <p>Sizes 4 through 13, including half sizes. Our <a href="/pages/ring-size-guide">ring sizing guide</a> sets out two simple methods for measuring at home. Outside that range, write to us — we can usually accommodate.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>

    <div class="faqp-category">
      <h2 class="faqp-category__title">Orders &amp; delivery</h2>

      <details class="faqp-item">
        <summary class="faqp-question">How long does delivery take?</summary>
        <div class="faqp-answer">
          <p>Standard delivery arrives within five to seven business days from dispatch. Because each piece is finished to order, please allow an additional three to five business days in the atelier before shipment. Expedited options are offered at checkout.</p>
          <p>Full details on our <a href="/pages/shipping">Shipping &amp; Returns</a> page.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faqp-item">
        <summary class="faqp-question">Do you ship internationally?</summary>
        <div class="faqp-answer">
          <p>At present we ship within the United States. International delivery is being arranged — join the atelier list to be notified when it begins.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faqp-item">
        <summary class="faqp-question">What does delivery cost?</summary>
        <div class="faqp-answer">
          <p>Delivery is complimentary, fully insured, on every order — no minimum. Expedited options are offered at checkout for sooner arrival.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faqp-item">
        <summary class="faqp-question">Is my order insured in transit?</summary>
        <div class="faqp-answer">
          <p>Always. Every shipment is fully insured from the moment it leaves our atelier until it is in your hand. If anything happens in transit, we take care of it.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>

    <div class="faqp-category">
      <h2 class="faqp-category__title">Returns, resizing &amp; warranty</h2>

      <details class="faqp-item">
        <summary class="faqp-question">What is your return policy?</summary>
        <div class="faqp-answer">
          <p>A thirty-day return window from delivery, on unworn pieces in their original packaging with the certificate intact. Write to <a href="mailto:hello@lauramilman.com">hello@lauramilman.com</a> within thirty days and we will provide a prepaid return label. Refunds are processed within five to seven business days of receipt. Bespoke commissions and engraved pieces are final sale.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faqp-item">
        <summary class="faqp-question">Do you offer a warranty?</summary>
        <div class="faqp-answer">
          <p>Yes — a lifetime warranty against manufacturing defects on every Laura Milman setting. It covers defects in materials and workmanship from the moment a piece leaves our atelier. Ordinary wear, accidental damage, and loss are not covered, but can be addressed through a paid repair. For care, see our <a href="/pages/care-guide">care guide</a>.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faqp-item">
        <summary class="faqp-question">What if my ring does not fit?</summary>
        <div class="faqp-answer">
          <p>The first resizing is complimentary within thirty days of delivery. Write to <a href="mailto:hello@lauramilman.com">hello@lauramilman.com</a> and we will arrange the exchange and shipping in both directions. Most resizings are completed and returned within five to seven business days. Subsequent resizings are offered at cost.</p>
          <p>To choose the right size from the start, see our <a href="/pages/ring-size-guide">ring sizing guide</a>.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>

    <div class="faqp-category">
      <h2 class="faqp-category__title">Pricing &amp; payment</h2>

      <details class="faqp-item">
        <summary class="faqp-question">Why are lab-grown stones less expensive than mined ones?</summary>
        <div class="faqp-answer">
          <p>Lab-grown production removes the costly extraction process and the long supply chain that follows it. Typically thirty to seventy percent below mined stones of equivalent grade — a difference that can mean a larger centre stone, a higher cut grade, or a more elaborate setting from the atelier without changing your budget.</p>
          <p>Lower price does not mean lower quality. The same brilliance, the same hardness, the same IGI / GIA grading. More on the value calculation in our <a href="/pages/why-lab-grown">On Diamond Origin</a> page.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faqp-item">
        <summary class="faqp-question">Do you offer payment plans?</summary>
        <div class="faqp-answer">
          <p>Yes. Shop Pay installments allow you to split your purchase into four interest-free payments at checkout, with no fees. Suitable for orders within a defined range, set by Shop Pay.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>

    <div class="faqp-cta">
      <h2 class="faqp-cta__title">Still have a question?</h2>
      <p class="faqp-cta__text">The atelier responds to every message personally, within 24 hours on business days.</p>
      <a href="mailto:hello@lauramilman.com" class="faqp-cta__btn">Write to the atelier</a>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

